{{infobox country at games | NOC = GHA | NOCname = Ghana Olympic Committee | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1952 | flagcaption = Flag of the [[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]] | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Helsinki]] | competitors = 7 (all men) | sports = 1 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
The '''[[Gold Coast (British colony)|Gold Coast]]''' along with '''[[British Togoland]]''', now known as [[Ghana]], competed at the '''[[1952 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Helsinki]], [[Finland]]. Seven competitors, all men, took part in five events in one sport.<ref name="sports-reference">{{cite web|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/GHA/summer/1952/ |title=Ghana at the 1952 Helsinki Summer Games |accessdate=2012-07-14 |work=sports-reference.com |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121216200144/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/GHA/summer/1952/ |archivedate=2012-12-16 |df= }}</ref> It was the first appearance of the [[West Africa]]n nation, which didn't win a medal at its debut.
==Results by event== ===[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics|Athletics]]=== '''[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's 100 metres|Men's 100 metres]]''' * [[Gabriel Laryea]] :* Round 1 &mdash; 11.1 s (→ 3rd in heat, did not advance) * [[George Acquaah]] :* Round 1 &mdash; 11.2 s (→ 5th in heat, did not advance)
'''[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's 800 metres|Men's 800 metres]]''' * [[Mohamed Sanni-Thomas]] :* Round 1 &mdash; 2:05.8 min (→ 6th in heat, did not advance)
'''[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's 4 × 100 metres relay|Men's 4x100 metres relay]]''' * [[Gabriel Laryea]], [[George Acquaah]], [[John Owusu]], [[Augustus Lawson]] :* Round 1 &mdash; 42.1 s (→ 4th in heat, did not advance)
'''[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's high jump|Men's high jump]]''' * [[James Owoo]] :* Qualification &mdash; 187 cm (→ advanced to the final) :* Final &mdash; 180 cm (→ 20th place)
'''[[Athletics at the 1952 Summer Olympics – Men's triple jump|Men's triple jump]]''' * [[William Lang (Ghanaian athlete)|William Laing]] :* Qualification &mdash; 14.09 m (→ did not advance)
