The '''Luxembourg Athletics Federation''' ({{lang-fr|Fédération Luxembourgeoise d’Athlétisme}}), abbreviated to '''FLA''', is the [[Sport governing body|governing body]] for the sport of [[Athletics (sport)|athletics]] in [[Luxembourg]]. It was founded on 11 November 1928, replacing the Federation of Luxembourgian Athletic Sports Societies ({{lang-fr|Fédération des Sociétés Luxembourgeoises des Sports Athlétiques}}).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fla.lu/histoire/history.htm |title=History |accessdate=2007-07-26 |last= |first= |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=22 July 2007 |publisher=Luxembourg Athletics Federation }}</ref>
==List of presidents== * [[Edmond Marx]] (1928–1940) * [[Alex Servais]] (1945–1947) * [[Jos Lucius]] (1947–1958) * [[Pierre Wies]] (1958) * [[Jos Lucius]] (1959) * [[Emile Goebel]] (1960–1961) * [[François Mersch]] (1961–1962) * [[Josy Barthel]] (1962–1972) * [[Norbert Haupert]] (1973–1979) * [[Mil Jung]] (1980–1989) * [[Jean-Marie Janssen]] (1991–2000) * [[Alex Bodry]] (2001 – 2010) * [[Claude Haagen]] (2010 - Present Day)
