{{Infobox football club | clubname = Mbao FC | image = Mbao FC - Kagera Sugar 2016-2017.jpg | caption = Vodacom Premier League match between Mbao FC and [[Kagera Sugar]], played at [[CCM Kirumba Stadium]] in [[Mwanza]] on November 3rd, 2016. Mbao FC are in blue. | fullname = Mbao Football club | nickname = | founded = 2005 | ground = [[CCM Kirumba Stadium]], Kitangiri [[Mwanza]], [[Tanzania]]| | capacity = 35,000 | chairman = Solly Zephania Njashi | Secretary = Daniel Naila | manager = Amri Said | league = [[Tanzanian Premier League]] | season = | position = | pattern_la1 = | pattern_b1 = | pattern_ra1 = | pattern_sh1 = | pattern_so1 = | leftarm1 = | body1 = | rightarm1 = | shorts1 = | socks1 = | website = }} '''Mbao FC''' is a [[Football (soccer)|football]] club from [[Mwanza]], [[Tanzania]]. 'Mbao' is the Swahili word for 'wood'.
==Achievements==
===2015/2016===
They won promotion to the [[Tanzanian Premier League]] after the 2015/2016 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mbao FC Promoted to Premier League|url=http://allafrica.com/stories/201604240056.html|website=AllAfrica|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref> ===2016/2017===
In the 2016/2017 season they are one of two teams from [[Mwanza]] playing in the Premier League. The other being [[Toto African]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Vodacom Premier League Standings|url=https://www.fifa.com/live-scores/nationalleagues/nationalleague=tanzania-premier-league-2000000151/standings/index.html|website=FIFA|accessdate=13 October 2016}}</ref> ===2017===
In May 2017, Mbao FC played the final of the Azam Sports Federation Cup, against [[Simba Sports Club]]. Simba won the game 2–1 in extra time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Simba, Mbao match grosses Sh117m|url=http://www.thecitizen.co.tz/News/Sports/Simba--Mbao-match-grosses-Sh117m--/1840572-3947026-hh0qs2/index.html|website=The Citizen|accessdate=27 August 2017}}</ref>
They play their home games at [[CCM Kirumba Stadium]]. ==References== {{reflist}}
