'''Youssouf Yacoub M'Changama''' (born August 29, 1990) is a [[Comoros|Comorian]] professional footballer who currently plays for [[Grenoble Foot 38]].<ref name=oldhamsign>{{cite web|title=Latics Sign International|url=http://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/page/NewsUpdate/0,,10337~2634710,00.html|publisher=Oldham Athletic AFC|accessdate=6 May 2012|date=5 March 2012}}</ref>
==Club career== M'Changama made his Latics, and [[Football League]], debut as a substitute against [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]], on 10 March 2012, making him the first Comorian ever to play for the club.<ref name="bbc17243475">{{cite news | title = Oldham 1 - 2 Yeovil | url = https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17243475 | work = BBC Sport | publisher = British Broadcasting Corporation | date = 10 March 2012 | accessdate = 10 March 2012}}</ref>
